Sentencas: Adding Ni-coated graphite particulates to a tape casting colloidal suspension is capable of creating a sintered solid oxide fuel cell anode with a critical percolation threshold for conductivity significantly lower than conventional anode materials.
Titulo: Development of solid oxide fuel cell anodes using metal-coated pore-forming agents

Sentencas: For example, conductivity at 800degreesC reached over 1200 Omega(-1).cm(-1) in these anodes at a Ni volume below the percolation threshold reported for conventional anode materials.
Titulo: Development of solid oxide fuel cell anodes using metal-coated pore-forming agents

Sentencas: This behavior was explained based on an effective Ni content, V-Nieff, which includes the graphite portion of the particle.
Titulo: Development of solid oxide fuel cell anodes using metal-coated pore-forming agents

Sentencas: In the green tape, V-Nieff, controls the creation of a percolating network of Ni.
Titulo: Development of solid oxide fuel cell anodes using metal-coated pore-forming agents

Sentencas: However, when the graphite burns away, it leaves a percolated Ni network at a much lower volume fraction than would otherwise be required.
Titulo: Development of solid oxide fuel cell anodes using metal-coated pore-forming agents
